{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"CONTAINER review (G3 — child coverage), parent c81c (plan-review fan-out optimization), child under review = S6/da34 (fidelity-eval harness). 4-bucket audit of the parent's acceptance/success criteria against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 0250, S2 c6e5, S3 ba7e, S4 98c6, S5 1762, S6 da34).\n\nCOVERAGE MAP (parent criterion -> bucket / covering child):\n- AC1 \"all six children closed\" -> STRUCTURAL (aggregate; not a single-child obligation).\n- AC2 \"8-child review in minutes / lower token cost / cache reads non-zero\" -> FULLY by siblings S3 (parallelize) + S1 (cache reads) + S4/S5 (call reduction); NOT S6's job — no absence.\n- AC3 \"caching provider-safe (openai/gemini unchanged)\" -> FULLY by siblings S1 + S2 — no absence.\n- AC4 / Success \"findings remain within OFFLINE-eval tolerance of current per-child behavior / preserve-or-improve fidelity (no regression)\" -> S6 is the SOLE/named fidelity instrument => see FINDING below (PARTIAL).\n- AC5 \"make lint + full suite pass\" -> FULLY by S6's own AC6 (and each sibling's lint/test AC).\n\nNo FALSE absence: every parent criterion S6 does not own is covered by a named sibling.\n\nFINDING (G3 — partial coverage / qualifier mismatch on the parent fidelity criterion):\n- [ ] The parent's fidelity acceptance criterion is worded \"Findings remain within OFFLINE-eval tolerance of the current per-child behavior,\" but S6 — the only child that can cover it — builds the actual fidelity measurement (finding-recall + G3/G4-attribution vs baseline, via parity.py) as the LIVE SEMANTIC eval, which S6 explicitly makes OPT-IN / workflow_dispatch / NON-BLOCKING and \"NEVER a required CI status check.\" S6's OFFLINE check is the deterministic spec/grader-DISCIPLINE check (no model, no finding recall) — it does NOT measure fidelity. So the parent AC4 as literally worded (\"within offline-eval tolerance\") is covered by NO child: the offline check measures spec validity, not fidelity, and the fidelity measure is live + non-blocking.\n  criteria: [G3]\n  location: parent c81c \"Acceptance Criteria\" bullet 4 (\"Findings remain within offline-eval tolerance...\") + \"Success Criteria\"; child da34 \"CI posture\" + ACs 1/2/4; sibling 98c6/1762 \"CI/eval posture (S6)\" (\"HUMAN-REVIEWED development gate... NOT a required/blocking CI check\").\n  evidence: [\"Parent AC4: 'Findings remain within offline-eval tolerance of the current per-child behavior (no fidelity regression).'\", \"da34 AC1: offline discipline check is 'deterministic, runs on every PR' — spec validity + grader discipline, explicitly 'no model'.\", \"da34 AC4: 'The LIVE semantic eval is OPT-IN (workflow_dispatch / path-scoped) and NON-BLOCKING — NOT a required CI status check; documented as a human-reviewed development gate for S4/S5.'\", \"98c6 remediation: 'Fidelity gate = the S6 semantic eval harness (DEPENDS ON S6), not a vague offline eval.'\"]\n  scenarios: [\"Epic closes with S6's offline discipline check green on every PR but the live semantic fidelity eval never run (opt-in/non-blocking) -> parent AC4 ('within offline-eval tolerance') is reportable as MET while no finding-fidelity comparison was actually performed; a fidelity regression in S4/S5 ships unmeasured.\", \"Verifier reads parent AC4 literally, looks for an OFFLINE fidelity-tolerance gate, finds only an offline SPEC-DISCIPLINE check + a live non-blocking eval -> cannot point to any child that closes AC4 as worded.\"]\n  impact: \"The parent's headline fidelity criterion (the whole reason S4/S5 are eval-gated) is only PARTIALLY covered by its sole intended consumer: S6 supplies the fidelity measure but reclassifies it as live + non-blocking, while the on-every-PR OFFLINE check it does run measures spec discipline, not findings. The parent AC as literally worded ('offline-eval tolerance') maps to nothing the roster enforces, so 'no fidelity regression' can be marked satisfied without ever measuring fidelity.\";\n  checklist_item: \"The union of children covers each parent acceptance/success criterion — 4-bucket audit; an uncovered criterion is a finding.\"\n  suggested_fix: \"Reconcile the parent AC4 wording with S6's actual mechanism: either (a) re-word parent AC4 to 'within SEMANTIC-eval tolerance, measured by the S6 live recall/attribution diff (human-reviewed dev gate before merging S4/S5)' so the criterion names the live, non-blocking instrument that S6 actually builds; and/or (b) add to S6 the explicit obligation that the live semantic eval MUST be run and pass-within-tolerance as the gate for closing S4 and S5 (so 'no fidelity regression' is an enforced gate, not an optional one). Keep S6's offline discipline check as spec-validity only, distinct from the fidelity tolerance.\""},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782578715143742001,"uuid":"5541eb6f-688f-4a0c-bb0b-2b212001121e"}